# 8-3. T-Shirt: Write a function called make_shirt() that accepts a size and the text of a message 
# that should be printed on the shirt. The function should print a sentence summarizing the size of 
# the shirt and the message printed on it.

# Call the function once using positional arguments to make a shirt. Call the function a second time using keyword arguments.

def make_shirt(size, message):
    print(f"You ordered a {size} shirt that will say {message}")

make_shirt("XL","Hello World")

size1 = input("What size shirt do you want? ")
message1 = input("What do you want it to say? ")

make_shirt(size1, message1)
